{"TopicId":191231,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"What editor for kOS?","CreatedByName":"RizzoTheRat","CreatedById":123362,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-27T10:07:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RizzoTheRat","CreatedById":123362,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-27T10:07:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m currently restructuring all the kOS code I\u0027ve written over the last year or more of playing with it, and up to now have been using Notepad\u002B\u002B with the Kerboscript Bright style addon to highlight code for me.\u00A0 I originally went with this as I was already familiar with Notepad\u002B\u002B, but now is probably a good time to see what other options are worthwhile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are several other options mentioned on the Github post about editors \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/KSP-KOS/EditorTools\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/KSP-KOS/EditorTools\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone\u0027s suggested using VSCode to me, with a KSP language addon that should automatically pick up my common mistakes like forgetting to put a full stop at the end of the line \u003Ca href=\u0022https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=JohnChabot.kos-vscode\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=JohnChabot.kos-vscode\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot being a software developer (I learned programming in Fortran 77 and QBasic!) I\u0027m not familiar with what modern \u0022developer environments\u0022 can do compared with basic text editors.\u00A0 Any recommendations?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkNounours","CreatedById":191261,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-01T12:46:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi. I use Sublime Text but you can use Atom, Notepad\u002B\u002B.....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-01T13:51:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use Notepad\u002B\u002B\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor everything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-01T15:09:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this isnt *specifically* related to your original question, but while shopping around for different editors, if anyone finds that it comes down to not much difference between NotePad\u002B\u002B and others, and if you also do a lot of config/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patchi editing/creating as well as kOS\u00A0 scripting, there\u0027s also this superb KSP Config language for NPP which \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E maintains.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/JadeOfMaar/NPP_KSPlang\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/JadeOfMaar/NPP_KSPlang\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust thought I\u0027d throw that out as a variable, towards going with NPP, if for no other reason vOv\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-01T18:06:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nNotepad\u002B\u002B\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAtom\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nVS Code\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nNotepad\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ManEatingApe","CreatedById":151354,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-01T22:11:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSheesh, kids these days, it has to be \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0